blindfold /ˈblaɪndˌfəʊld/

1. N-COUNT A blindfold is a strip of cloth that is tied over someone's eyes so that they cannot see. 蒙眼布 

2. V-T If you blindfold someone, you tie a blindfold over their eyes. 用布蒙住眼睛 

例： His abductors blindfolded him and drove him to an apartment in southern Beirut. 绑架者们用布蒙住了他的眼睛，把他载到了贝鲁特南部的一套公寓。

